casebody.data:
ROSE v. WARDEN OF THE MARYLAND HOUSE OF CORRECTION [App. No. 31,

September Term, 1964.]

Decided October 16, 1964.

Before Henderson, C. J., and Prescott, Marbury, Sybert and Oppenheimer, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Application for leave to appeal from a denial of post conviction relief is denied for the reasons set out in the opinion of Judge Jones in the court below.

Application denied.
